    <h3 id = "intro"> You also said that <%=@lowest_ratio_response%> was the career with the lowest female to male ratio. The correct answer was Computer Science!
    The wage gap is currently 20%, which means that (on average) women are earning only 80% of their male counterparts. You guessed that the wage gap was <%=@wage_gap_response%>%.
    Scientists approximate that it will take an average of 41 years for the wage gap to go away. Your guess was <%=@pay_parity_response%> years. </h3>
      <p id = "intro">Teachers who teach elementary and middle school are paid $56,420 per year, and highschool teachers get $58,170 per year. The pay isn't very high, which is unfair since they shape our modern society into how it is today. They teach boys and girls the basics of math, science, history, english, and many other subjects. Without teachers, people would be uneducated and unable make good decisions for themselves and others. Teachers are extremely important to society!</p> <br> <br>
    
