      <li id = "gap">Highschool teachers are paid more than elementary and middle school teachers. This is because women (and girls pursuing the career) are encouraged to take care of younger children, and men to teach older students. Women are usually told that they would be better with handling young students, when really it depends on the person's unique abilities and character. </li>
    
      
  <p id = "gap">The wage gap may be unfair, but there are many ways to improve and reduce it! An idea to overcome this gap is to learn how to negotiate your salary, which is not usually taught in college courses. Men and women should also teach whatever age they have the skills to teach, not relying on societal stereotypes to decide that for them.</p>
    
    <h2 id = "cons">The Cons of Being a Teacher</h2>
    
    <li id = "bad">Low payment, as mentioned before. Teachers often have to use their own money to do activity lessons and to buy the supplies they need, such as dry erase markers, scissors, etc.</li> <br>
    
    <li id = "bad">Payment between highschool, elementary, and middle school teachers is not equal. On average, highschool teachers are paid more than other teachers, because almost half of them are male. They work the same amount of time and do the same job, but women make 9% less than men.</li> <br>
    
